<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-11T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="1040" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1040">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00 Revolution 1931/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Funchal</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Huddleston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-11T14:00:00-05:00">April 11, 1931—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram April 10, 4 p.m. The Department has been caused no
                            embarrassment of which it is aware and perceives no reason why an
                            apology should be necessary.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>